<TITLE> Mirza Abbas, Babar, Silver Selim freed on bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com)  Mirza Abbas, former minister for housing and works, Lutfuzzaman Babar, former state minister for home and former BNP MP MAH Selim, better known as 'Silver' Selim, have been freed on bail on Thursday evening. Deputy inspector general, prisons, Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui said, "Mirza Abbas was freed from the central jail and Babar and Silver Selim were released from the prison cells of the Bangabandhu Medical College University hospital." Selim, Abbas and Babar were arrested on March 7, Feb. 25 and May 8, 2007, respectively. bdnew
